	<div class="pageBoxHeader"><img src="images/header_jobs.gif" width="241" height="31" border="0" alt="Jobs at Tower Theatre"></div>
	<div class="pageBox"><span class="fontMedium"><br>We are looking for smart, friendly people who are passionate about the films we show and are dedicated to making the Angelika the most dynamic and comfortable cinema in New York City.  Here's a list of jobs that are available.<br><br /></span>


<hr noshade size=1 class="pageBoxInsetHR"><img src="images/header_description.gif" width="271" height="19" border="0" alt="">
<br />
		<table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=5 border=0 class="pageBoxInset"><tr><td>
		<span class="fontLarge"><font size=4>Service Associates (Concession, Box Office & Usher)</font></span><br><span class="fontMedium"><b><br></b>
We are looking for team members who love the films we show and are dedicated to making every visit to the Angelika enjoyable.   Our Angelika Team Members are responsible for providing each customer with individualized attention and friendly service.   We are looking for team members who have excellent interpersonal and strong customer service skills and commitment to our mission of making the Angelika the best cinema experience in New York.  Previous retail (cinema, hotel, restaurant or retail industry) experience would be a plus, however we are willing to train team members who display pride and an attitude and desire to provide our customers with the best service.<br>
		<br><b>Contact:</b>Cinema Managing Director<br>
		<b>Phone:</b>212-995-2570                                                                                        <br>
		<b>E-Mail:</b> <a href="mailto:angelika.nyc@readingrdi.com" class="link2">angelika.nyc@readingrdi.com</a><br></td></tr></table>
		
		
		<hr noshade size=1 class="pageBoxInsetHR"><img src="images/header_description.gif" width="271" height="19" border="0" alt="">
<br />
		<table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=5 border=0 class="pageBoxInset"><tr><td>
		<span class="fontLarge"><b>Calling all Projectionists / Assistant Managers!</b></span><br><span class="fontMedium">The Angelika New York and City Cinemas is seeking skilled Projectionists / Assistant Managers!  Candidates must have previous projection and/or management experience, and must be available nights, weekends and holidays.<br><br>Starting salary is $10 per hour, depending on experience.  Benefits include free movies, free popcorn & soda, concession & café discounts, flexible schedule, and advancement opportunity.<br><br>If interested, please fax your resume to: (212) 871-9093.<br>
		<br><b>Contact:</b><br>
		<b>Phone:</b>                                                                                                    <br>
		<b>E-Mail:</b> <a href="mailto:" class="link2"></a><br></td></tr></table>
		
		
		<hr noshade size=1 class="pageBoxInsetHR"><img src="images/header_description.gif" width="271" height="19" border="0" alt="">
<br />
		<table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=5 border=0 class="pageBoxInset"><tr><td>
		<span class="fontLarge"><FONT SIZE=4>Cinema Managing Director</FONT></span><br><span class="fontMedium"><b>This position is currently filled. Please check back for availability.</b><br><br>The cinema managing director will be responsible for all aspects of an efficient and profitable cinema operation, including the development of a team dedicated to making the Angelika the best cinema experience in New York.  Specific responsibilities include: <br>
 
<li>	Overseeing all facets of cinema operations 
<li>	Cinema staff supervision
<li>	Developing and maintaining a team oriented environment 
<li>	Ensuring that profit and productivity goals are met through developing business plans, managing payroll hours, sales and P&L
<li>	Ensuring that concession items are merchandised and presented in a way to maximize sales
<li>	Interviewing and selection 
<li>	Training and developing staff 
<li>	Concession, merchandise and inventory management
<li>	Communication between the cinema and the home office 
<li>	Maintaining the Angelika commitment to a strong New York community presence
<li>	Assuring that all cinema administrative functions are carried out in a timely manner 
<br>
<br>
Qualified candidates should possess an entrepreneurial spirit, a knowledge and love of film, especially independent and foreign films, and a sincere desire to make a difference.  Qualified candidates should have at least two years experience in the retail industry (cinema, hotel, restaurant or retail industry).  College is preferred.   Due to the nature of our business, weekend and holiday work is required.   Specific skills we are looking for include:
<li>	Strong supervisory skills 
<li>	Ability to lead, motivate and develop staff
<li>	Commitment to superior customer service
<li>	Ability to work autonomously and as part of a team
<li>	Strong commitment to ensuring that profit and productivity standards are met
<li>	Flexibility and problem solving ability
<li>	Enthusiasm and strong interpersonal skills 
<li>	Superior organizational skills 
<li>	Excellent verbal and written communication skills
<li>	Ability to handle pressure and work long hours when necessary 
<li>	Computer skills, including familiarity with spreadsheets and word processing<br>
		<br><b>Contact:</b>Terri Moore<br>
		<b>Phone:</b>212-871-6828                                                                                        <br>
		<b>E-Mail:</b> <a href="mailto:angelikany@readingrdi.com" class="link2">angelikany@readingrdi.com</a><br></td></tr></table>
		
		
		
